NMR data preprocessing

Introduction

This tutorial will guide you through the preprocessing of NMR data using the metabom8 package in R. We will cover data reading, visualization, calibration, alignment, baseline correction, and normalization.

Download data

Download here

Prerequisites

Before starting, ensure that you have the following packages installed:

  • devtools
  • metabom8

You can install these packages using the following commands:

install.packages('devtools')
devtools::install_github('tkimhofer/metabom8', force = TRUE)

Setting the Working Directory

Set your working directory to the location of your NMR data files:

setwd('/Volumes/AEIWZ A/Project/AG-Bio')

Reading the FID Files

Specify the path to your data and read the FID files. Here we assume the pulse program is cpmgpr1d.

library(metabom8)

path = 'Leaf'
read1d_proc(path, exp_type = list(PULPROG='cpmgpr1d'))

dim(X)
## [1]    31 65536
length(ppm)
## [1] 65536

Plotting Spectra

You can plot single spectra or multiple spectra for visual assessment:

# Plot single spectrum
spec(X[1,], ppm, shift = range(ppm), interactive = F)

# Plot multiple spectra
matspec(X, ppm, shift = range(ppm), interactive = F)

Creating Run Order

Create a run order based on the acquisition date:

meta$runOrder = rank(as.POSIXct(meta$a_DATE))

TSP Signal Plotting

Overlay TSP signals while considering facets, colors, and line types:

specOverlay(X, ppm, shift=c(-0.05, 0.05),  
            an=list('Facet'=meta$a_EXP, 
                     'RunOrder'=meta$runOrder, 
                     'Pulse Program'=meta$a_PULPROG))

TSP Calibration

Perform TSP calibration and plot the calibrated spectra:

X_cal = calibrate(X, ppm, type='tsp')
matspec(X_cal, ppm, shift=c(-0.1, 0.1), interactive=FALSE)

Alignment of Peaks

Align the peaks in the spectra:

Xal = alignSegment(X)
matspec(Xal, ppm, shift=c(9, 11), interactive=FALSE, main='LowField Cap')

matspec(Xal, ppm, shift=c(-1, 1), interactive=FALSE, main='UpField Cap')

Indexing and Excision of Noise Regions

Identify TSP and noise regions, and excise them from the data:

idx_tsp = get_idx(range=c(min(ppm), 1), ppm)
idx_noise = get_idx(range=c(9.5, max(ppm)), ppm)

idx_rm = c(idx_tsp, idx_noise)
X_cut = Xal[, -idx_rm]
ppm = ppm[-idx_rm]

Baseline Correction

Apply baseline correction and compare the results visually:

X_bl = bcor(X_cut)
Xcompare = rbind(X_bl[1, ], X_cut[1, ])
matspec(Xcompare, ppm, shift=c(7, 9), interactive=FALSE)

matspec(Xcompare, ppm, shift=c(3, 4), interactive=FALSE)

PQN Normalization

Perform PQN normalization and visualize the dilution coefficients:

X_pqn = pqn(X_bl, add_DilF = 'dilf')
hist(dilf, xlab='PQN calculated dilution factor')
